      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/12/6",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ اَلْحِنْطَةِ وَ اَلشَّعِيرِ أَشْتَرِي زَرْعَهُ قَبْلَ أَنْ يُسَنْبِلَ وَ هُوَ حَشِيشٌ قَالَ \"لاَ إِلاَّ أَنْ يَشْتَرِيَهُ لِقَصِيلٍ يَعْلِفُهُ اَلدَّوَابَّ ثُمَّ يَتْرُكَهُ إِنْ شَاءَ حَتَّى يُسَنْبِلَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3866 - It is narrated from Ali bin Abi Hamzah, from Abu Basir, from Abu Abdillah (as), who said: I asked him about purchasing wheat and barley crops before they produce spikes while they are still grass.\nImam (as) said: \"No, unless he buys it as fodder to feed animals, and then, if he wishes, he may leave it until it produces spikes.\""
        ]
      }
    },
